Park Chae-won.

257
00:15:56,789 --> 00:15:58,623
<i>Thanks to you,</i>

258
00:15:58,624 --> 00:16:00,960
<i>I've hit 500,000 followers.</i>

259
00:16:01,502 --> 00:16:02,753
<i>Thank you so much.</i>

260
00:16:18,352 --> 00:16:23,481
As you can see,
she seems to be a very popular influencer.

261
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:26,610
Don't you think this might cause trouble
if we get involved?

262
00:16:27,194 --> 00:16:28,319
That's more work for us.

263
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:29,654
Don't worry about that.

264
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:32,532
Minister Choi has agreed
to take full responsibility.

265
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:33,574
I see.

266
00:16:33,575 --> 00:16:36,328
600,000 followers.

267
00:16:36,829 --> 00:16:37,830
You punk...

268
00:16:40,582 --> 00:16:42,751
Do it! Of course we should do it!

269
00:16:43,252 --> 00:16:45,754
Whether 600,000 or six million,
we must do what we must.

270
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:47,505
That's right! Do it!

271
00:16:47,506 --> 00:16:48,923
Deputy Bong, get ready too.

272
00:16:48,924 --> 00:16:51,175
What's my role this time around?

273
00:16:51,176 --> 00:16:54,346
Why do you even ask?
Obviously, you'll go undercover as a girl.

274
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:57,182
What? Are you serious?

275
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,527
Why are you taking it so seriously?

276
00:17:10,070 --> 00:17:11,863
Am I really dressing up as a girl?

277
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:13,449
If so, would you?

278
00:17:14,241 --> 00:17:15,617
Why even consider it?

279
00:17:17,244 --> 00:17:18,829
Deputy Bong, provide backup.

280
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:21,748
Inspector Na, get out into the field now.

281
00:17:21,749 --> 00:17:23,291
It won't be me this time.

282
00:17:23,292 --> 00:17:25,668
Who else, then?
You're the only inspector we have.

283
00:17:25,669 --> 00:17:27,212
I've hired a new one.

284
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:33,844
<i>She's perfect for this case,
so why don't you just see how she does?</i>

285
00:17:40,726 --> 00:17:44,062
Ta-da! I drew Ye-ri. What do you think?
Looks like her, doesn't it?

286
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:48,691
By the way, everyone,
So-yeong keeps insisting I'm like a cat.

287
00:17:48,692 --> 00:17:53,322
This is Ms. Im Han-rim,
our student teacher here for training.

288
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:57,159
- Please introduce yourself.
- Okay.

289
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,410
Hello.

290
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:02,914
My name is Im Han-rim, and I teach math.

291
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:05,583
Depending on how you all behave,

292
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:07,543
I can become an angel,

293
00:18:07,544 --> 00:18:09,670
or I can become a devil.

294
00:18:09,671 --> 00:18:11,173
I hope we get along well.

295
00:18:14,384 --> 00:18:16,136
I'll take attendance.

296
00:18:16,887 --> 00:18:17,888
Kang Da-yeon.

297
00:18:18,388 --> 00:18:20,057
Kim Ye-rin.

298
00:18:20,641 --> 00:18:23,392
I don't think the front teeth
look the same.

299
00:18:23,393 --> 00:18:25,686
- No, they do.
- Don't they look the same?

300
00:18:25,687 --> 00:18:29,315
Guys, they're selecting uniform models
from Soyeon Girls' High this time.

301
00:18:29,316 --> 00:18:31,151
Our uniform is particularly pretty.

302
00:18:34,196 --> 00:18:36,322
No, I'm completely asymmetrical.

303
00:18:36,323 --> 00:18:38,616
I just always film my left side,

304
00:18:38,617 --> 00:18:40,661
but if I move the camera to my right...

305
00:18:49,795 --> 00:18:50,629
Miss.

306
00:18:51,338 --> 00:18:52,172
Yes?

307
00:18:52,881 --> 00:18:53,882
Ms. Im.

308
00:18:54,508 --> 00:18:56,134
Yes, what is it?

309
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:57,469
Do you have a boyfriend?

310
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:02,265
I do not.

311
00:19:02,266 --> 00:19:04,434
Why not? You're so pretty.

312
00:19:05,018 --> 00:19:06,019
Your cosmetic surgery...

313
00:19:06,770 --> 00:19:08,230
- It was done really well.
- Hey.

314
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:11,023
You probably spent
well over ten million won.

315
00:19:11,024 --> 00:19:13,651
Can we see a before photo
to see how well it turned out?

316
00:19:13,652 --> 00:19:16,028
Guys, aren't you curious? Aren't you?

317
00:19:16,029 --> 00:19:25,497
Show us!

318
00:19:34,548 --> 00:19:35,673
Yes.

319
00:19:35,674 --> 00:19:37,676
I've had cosmetic surgery.

320
00:19:38,802 --> 00:19:40,012
Breast reduction surgery.

321
00:19:41,054 --> 00:19:43,849
I like playing sports,
and they got in the way.

322
00:19:44,725 --> 00:19:46,601
So I got them done.

323
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:49,020
But it seems

324
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:53,983
no one in this class needs any reduction,

325
00:19:53,984 --> 00:19:56,570
so I won't take any further questions.

326
00:19:57,487 --> 00:19:59,322
Is she crazy? Who does she think she is?

327
00:19:59,323 --> 00:20:02,283
- So-yeong is so cheeky.
- Let's get back to the lesson.

328
00:20:02,284 --> 00:20:03,784
Before we do that,

329
00:20:03,785 --> 00:20:06,914
I think we need to collect
everyone's phones first.

330
00:20:08,290 --> 00:20:11,126
Everyone, hand in your phones!

331
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:12,752
She must be crazy.

332
00:20:12,753 --> 00:20:14,004
What does that mean?

333
00:20:14,588 --> 00:20:15,756
Is that a buzzword?

334
00:20:16,256 --> 00:20:18,925
You know I'm not up-to-date
with buzzwords.

335
00:20:18,926 --> 00:20:20,219
Even Reels...

336
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:23,180
Han Ye-ri.

337
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:25,599
Hand in your phone.

338
00:20:27,809 --> 00:20:30,187
I'm in the middle of a live stream.

339
00:20:30,854 --> 00:20:35,108
You're new, so you probably haven't heard,
but the principal gave me permission.

340
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:40,239
This is the last time.

341
00:20:40,864 --> 00:20:44,201
Hand in your phone.

342
00:20:46,328 --> 00:20:52,251
Then do you want to tell my fans yourself?

343
00:20:57,881 --> 00:20:59,925
IS THIS A LIVE BLOOPER?
COME BACK YE-RI

344
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:09,100
END THE LIVE STREAM?

345
00:21:09,101 --> 00:21:10,059
That scared me.

346
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:12,103
Are you crazy? What are you doing?

347
00:21:12,104 --> 00:21:13,981
It's the students who are crazy.

348
00:21:14,773 --> 00:21:18,150
The school is much more messed up
than I expected.

349
00:21:18,151 --> 00:21:21,028
Those who act like they're above teachers,

350
00:21:21,029 --> 00:21:23,740
those who treat teachers like toys,

351
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:27,369
and those who make fools of their teachers

352
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:31,915
will now be considered
to be in violation of teachers' rights.

353
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:34,500
I will always accept challenges,

354
00:21:34,501 --> 00:21:37,211
but you must be prepared
to face punishment.

355
00:21:37,212 --> 00:21:38,839
Ms. Im.

356
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:41,007
Aren't you overreacting?

357
00:21:41,008 --> 00:21:43,218
Let me introduce myself again.

358
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:47,096
I am Im Han-rim,
an inspector from the ERPB

359
00:21:47,097 --> 00:21:50,976
that operates
under Korea's Ministry of Education.

360
00:21:51,810 --> 00:21:53,561
From this moment on,

361
00:21:53,562 --> 00:21:57,523
I will severely punish
all violations of educational rights

362
00:21:57,524 --> 00:21:59,859
occurring here
at Soyeon Girls' High School.

363
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:02,487
Then I will destroy
the root causes of it all.

364
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:07,159
The first step to this is the phones!

365
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:11,663
Hand over your phones right this second!

366
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:39,482
I hope what you've just handed in
isn't a second phone or an inactive phone

367
00:22:39,483 --> 00:22:42,360
to fool teachers.

368
00:22:42,361 --> 00:22:44,820
For any students who have done so,

369
00:22:44,821 --> 00:22:47,741
for the final time, I will count to three.

370
00:22:50,660 --> 00:22:51,787
<i>One!</i>

371
00:22:52,954 --> 00:22:54,164
<i>Two!</i>

372
00:22:54,664 --> 00:22:55,874
Three!

373
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:05,092
PHONE POSSESSION WARNING

374
00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:20,606
<i>Attention students.</i>

375
00:23:20,607 --> 00:23:24,778
<i>There will now be an announcement
of special directives from the ERPB.</i>

376
00:23:27,406 --> 00:23:28,240
<i>First,</i>

377
00:23:29,241 --> 00:23:33,495
<i>Soyeon Girls' High School
now falls under the authority of the ERPB.</i>

378
00:23:36,373 --> 00:23:37,373
<i>Second,</i>

379
00:23:37,374 --> 00:23:41,837
<i>there are no restrictions whatsoever
on the ERPB's teaching methods.</i>

380
00:23:44,339 --> 00:23:45,298
<i>Third,</i>

381
00:23:45,799 --> 00:23:48,343
<i>you must always follow
the inspector's instructions.</i>

382
00:23:50,846 --> 00:23:51,888
<i>Fourth,</i>

383
00:23:52,472 --> 00:23:54,056
<i>in the event of insubordination,</i>

384
00:23:54,057 --> 00:23:56,977
<i>we will not be responsible
for any disadvantages that arise.</i>

385
00:23:57,686 --> 00:23:59,396
TEACHERS' MAIN OFFICE

386
00:24:02,732 --> 00:24:04,901
I'm here from the ERPB.

387
00:24:11,992 --> 00:24:13,410
- Attention!
- Did someone snitch?

388
00:24:14,619 --> 00:24:16,454
"In the event of insubordination,

389
00:24:16,455 --> 00:24:19,249
we won't be responsible
for any disadvantages that arise."

390
00:24:19,833 --> 00:24:21,125
You heard that, right?

391
00:24:21,126 --> 00:24:24,629
Everyone, report to the field!

392
00:24:25,797 --> 00:24:28,174
<i>Please write the details
on the form given to you.</i>

393
00:24:28,175 --> 00:24:32,428
It could be that you were falsely accused,
which led to defamation.

394
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:34,389
Or maybe you raised this issue,

395
00:24:34,890 --> 00:24:37,851
only to find yourself
being bullied by the students.

396
00:24:38,351 --> 00:24:42,355
Perhaps you're aware of colleagues
who are suffering online

397
00:24:43,231 --> 00:24:47,693
from leaked personal information,
judged appearances, and edited photos.

398
00:24:47,694 --> 00:24:49,321
But you're too scared of the kids,

399
00:24:49,905 --> 00:24:54,700
or maybe you have no choice
and have turned a blind eye.

400
00:24:54,701 --> 00:24:56,286
Whatever it may be,

401
00:24:57,829 --> 00:24:58,705
please tell us.

402
00:25:03,543 --> 00:25:08,839
May I take your silence as consent
to hand over full control to the ERPB?

403
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:11,592
Pardon? No, it's not that.

404
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:14,471
It means our school
doesn't have any problems.

405
00:25:15,138 --> 00:25:17,516
If adults fear children,

406
00:25:18,433 --> 00:25:20,101
the world is doomed.

407
00:25:20,977 --> 00:25:24,730
Don't you think it would be even worse
for teachers?

408
00:25:24,731 --> 00:25:26,899
TEACHERS' RIGHTS VIOLATIONS SURVEY

409
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:27,859
Well...

410
00:25:29,236 --> 00:25:30,904
Please don't think too hard.

411
00:25:31,696 --> 00:25:32,697
It's simple enough.

412
00:25:33,615 --> 00:25:36,116
If you think of anything later,
please write it down

413
00:25:36,117 --> 00:25:38,160
and give it to Inspector Im Han-rim or me.

414
00:25:38,161 --> 00:25:40,704
No chanting on the final repetition!

415
00:25:40,705 --> 00:25:43,083
- Proceed.
- Proceed.

416
00:25:46,670 --> 00:25:48,547
Please hand in the forms to me.

417
00:25:49,047 --> 00:25:51,174
I think that would be best.

418
00:25:53,635 --> 00:25:54,928
Six.

419
00:25:56,888 --> 00:25:57,973
Seven.

420
00:26:00,267 --> 00:26:01,726
Eight.

421
00:26:02,769 --> 00:26:03,728
Hey!

422
00:26:05,647 --> 00:26:06,773
Lift your damn heads up!

423
00:26:09,734 --> 00:26:10,693
One.

424
00:26:10,694 --> 00:26:12,279
SNACK BAR

425
00:26:13,238 --> 00:26:14,406
Unity!

426
00:26:15,949 --> 00:26:17,242
Look at you.

427
00:26:17,826 --> 00:26:19,703
Hey! Unity!

428
00:26:20,662 --> 00:26:21,537
Reporting, sir!

429
00:26:21,538 --> 00:26:25,249
Sergeant First Class, Im Han-rim,
Special Forces Reserve!

430
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:27,918
I have been assigned
to ERPB duty as of today!

431
00:26:27,919 --> 00:26:28,877
Unity!

432
00:26:28,878 --> 00:26:31,339
What's with the report between civilians?
At ease.

433
00:26:32,173 --> 00:26:33,466
Even so!

434
00:26:34,301 --> 00:26:35,135
Unity!

435
00:26:38,888 --> 00:26:39,972
Hey.

436
00:26:39,973 --> 00:26:41,223
My goodness.

437
00:26:41,224 --> 00:26:43,809
Hey, your disguise is great, Im Han-rim.

438
00:26:43,810 --> 00:26:45,269
No, don't. It's embarrassing.

439
00:26:45,270 --> 00:26:48,397
You haven't met yet, have you?

440
00:26:48,398 --> 00:26:49,481
Come here.

441
00:26:49,482 --> 00:26:52,443
This is Deputy Director Bong Geun-dae.

442
00:26:52,444 --> 00:26:53,862
It's "Deputy Bong" for short.

443
00:26:55,071 --> 00:26:56,239
Deputy Bong.

444
00:26:57,115 --> 00:26:58,450
He's not just any deputy.

445
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:02,536
You know KAIST, right?
He graduated from there in just two years.

446
00:27:02,537 --> 00:27:03,913
Wow, is that right?

447
00:27:04,956 --> 00:27:08,001
Nice to meet you.
I served in the same unit as Hwa-jin.

448
00:27:09,377 --> 00:27:10,462
Right...

449
00:27:11,379 --> 00:27:12,589
My name is Bong Geun-dae.

450
00:27:14,924 --> 00:27:16,008
What is it?

451
00:27:16,009 --> 00:27:17,344
What? What is it?

452
00:27:18,219 --> 00:27:20,347
I was sizing him up,
as it's our first meeting.

453
00:27:22,057 --> 00:27:24,934
Just be understanding, Deputy Bong.
She's a bit of a nutcase.

454
00:27:30,649 --> 00:27:32,232
So when will you tell me?

455
00:27:32,233 --> 00:27:33,525
Tell you what?

456
00:27:33,526 --> 00:27:37,488
You said you'd tell me why you hired me
once I started work.

457
00:27:37,489 --> 00:27:39,323
I just did. Because you're a nutcase.

458
00:27:39,324 --> 00:27:41,326
Is that really all?

459
00:27:45,622 --> 00:27:46,623
Here's a question.

460
00:27:47,707 --> 00:27:51,251
Kids are getting more cunning
and doing things that defy common sense.

461
00:27:51,252 --> 00:27:52,169
What should we do?

462
00:27:52,170 --> 00:27:54,296
Beat a nutcase with a nutcase. Am I right?

463
00:27:54,297 --> 00:27:55,214
That's right!

464
00:27:55,215 --> 00:27:57,132
Here, anything crazy goes!

465
00:27:57,133 --> 00:28:00,178
I like that a lot!

466
00:28:01,721 --> 00:28:02,597
However,

467
00:28:03,682 --> 00:28:05,684
remember one thing.

468
00:28:07,852 --> 00:28:10,145
You can't kill anyone. All right?

469
00:28:10,146 --> 00:28:11,814
If you feel the urge,

470
00:28:11,815 --> 00:28:16,653
write the Chinese character for "patience"
on your palm three times.

471
00:28:18,154 --> 00:28:18,988
Understood, sir.

472
00:28:20,156 --> 00:28:22,617
Is this the correct Chinese character
for "patience"?

473
00:28:23,368 --> 00:28:25,036
That's "benevolence."

474
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:27,413
Maybe you need a little benevolence.

475
00:28:27,414 --> 00:28:30,874
I know. Deputy Bong, you should teach her
how to write "patience."

476
00:28:30,875 --> 00:28:33,169
There's a lot you can learn from him.

477
00:28:33,670 --> 00:28:34,504
Try writing it.

478
00:28:37,841 --> 00:28:38,675
Well...

479
00:28:40,009 --> 00:28:40,843
PATIENCE

480
00:28:40,844 --> 00:28:44,179
"Cut your heart with a knife."

481
00:28:44,180 --> 00:28:47,182
This is how I memorized it for exams.

482
00:28:47,183 --> 00:28:49,436
Cut out the hearts of enemies!

483
00:28:51,104 --> 00:28:52,689
I've learned it. Thank you.

484
00:28:57,861 --> 00:28:58,737
Let's get to work.

485
00:28:59,863 --> 00:29:01,531
I'll do what I always do. Unity!

486
00:29:02,282 --> 00:29:04,200
- No more saluting.
- Understood, sir.

487
00:29:04,909 --> 00:29:06,034
I like your ribbon.

488
00:29:06,035 --> 00:29:07,746
Right. Damn it.

489
00:29:11,833 --> 00:29:12,667
Deputy Bong.

490
00:29:15,503 --> 00:29:17,254
It's Deputy Director Bong Geun-dae.

491
00:29:17,255 --> 00:29:20,800
Do you know the most dangerous place
in a girls' high school?

492
00:29:21,926 --> 00:29:22,969
No.

493
00:29:29,976 --> 00:29:31,186
It's right here.

494
00:29:32,353 --> 00:29:33,855
The snack bar.

495
00:29:34,981 --> 00:29:38,067
What's so dangerous about a snack bar?

496
00:29:40,612 --> 00:29:41,446
Work hard.

497
00:30:02,008 --> 00:30:04,803
Slow down!

498
00:30:06,179 --> 00:30:07,347
Move!

499
00:30:09,432 --> 00:30:10,683
No!

500
00:30:12,519 --> 00:30:15,063
Wait. You can't just open them
and eat them like that.

501
00:30:15,563 --> 00:30:17,105
Guys, you've got to pay!

502
00:30:17,106 --> 00:30:18,900
Pay up!

503
00:30:28,284 --> 00:30:30,369
Where are you all going right now?

504
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:31,745
Class is finished.

505
00:30:31,746 --> 00:30:33,414
You still have afternoon homeroom.

506
00:30:34,290 --> 00:30:35,499
That's not a thing here.

507
00:30:35,500 --> 00:30:36,709
What about cleaning?

508
00:30:43,049 --> 00:30:45,301
Our teacher told us not to.

509
00:30:46,010 --> 00:30:47,303
She said she'd do it.

510
00:30:50,682 --> 00:30:51,641
Didn't you?

511
00:30:52,851 --> 00:30:54,936
Well, I...

512
00:30:58,982 --> 00:31:01,776
Did you not see the special directives?

513
00:31:02,652 --> 00:31:05,113
If you mess with the inspector,
you're dead.

514
00:31:05,738 --> 00:31:07,073
Damn it.

515
00:31:09,033 --> 00:31:12,245
The people who use the space
are responsible for cleaning it.

516
00:31:17,709 --> 00:31:18,710
All right.

517
00:31:19,335 --> 00:31:21,336
No one is exempt.

518
00:31:21,337 --> 00:31:24,506
Today, we will begin "keeping house."

519
00:31:24,507 --> 00:31:27,468
- What is "keeping house"?
- Desks and chairs to the back.

520
00:31:27,969 --> 00:31:29,012
All the way back.

521
00:31:33,516 --> 00:31:35,518
All the way!

522
00:31:42,609 --> 00:31:46,821
Scrub the floors
until you can see your reflection.

523
00:31:54,370 --> 00:31:55,496
My socks...

524
00:31:58,249 --> 00:32:00,667
Ms. Im, are you sure this will be okay?

525
00:32:00,668 --> 00:32:03,254
The parents may protest...

526
00:32:14,641 --> 00:32:17,809
AFTER THE KO YEONG-SU INCIDENT,
SHE BECAME OUR TEACHER TO TORMENT US

527
00:32:17,810 --> 00:32:19,519
AND NOW SHE HAS CALLED ON THE ERPB

528
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:21,689
WE'RE ALL BEING FRAMED,
INCLUDING POOR YE-RI

529
00:32:30,073 --> 00:32:32,200
MINISTRY OF EDUCATION

530
00:32:40,583 --> 00:32:41,709
Hey!

531
00:32:42,210 --> 00:32:44,670
- Great work, sir!
- Great work today.

532
00:32:44,671 --> 00:32:48,173
I told you no saluting. We're civilians.

533
00:32:48,174 --> 00:32:49,466
Understood, sir.

534
00:32:49,467 --> 00:32:50,969
- Is this what I asked for?
- Yes.

535
00:32:51,469 --> 00:32:52,678
Anything noteworthy?

536
00:32:52,679 --> 00:32:55,348
- Well, my hand is...
- I was about to report to you.

537
00:32:56,057 --> 00:32:58,100
I think Ms. Jung is really scared.

538
00:32:58,101 --> 00:33:01,144
She was worried and asked
if it was okay to continue this.

539
00:33:01,145 --> 00:33:03,438
I'll meet with Ms. Jung.

540
00:33:03,439 --> 00:33:07,818
You check every student's social media
at the school.

541
00:33:07,819 --> 00:33:09,737
Find any slander about the teachers.

542
00:33:11,614 --> 00:33:12,489
You mean me, sir?

543
00:33:12,490 --> 00:33:14,199
- Why? Don't you want to?
- Yes, I do.

544
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:15,784
All right. Good luck with it.

545
00:33:15,785 --> 00:33:17,036
But my hand...

546
00:33:22,709 --> 00:33:23,584
Good luck.

547
00:33:26,796 --> 00:33:28,089
Deputy Bong.

548
00:33:30,383 --> 00:33:31,426
Deputy Director Bong.

549
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:35,763
Yes?

550
00:33:38,141 --> 00:33:42,602
I believe work is only done efficiently
with a command structure.

551
00:33:42,603 --> 00:33:44,856
You can just stay there and talk.

552
00:33:46,816 --> 00:33:49,027
I'm saying
there should be a chain of command.

553
00:33:50,069 --> 00:33:52,697
Right. What grade?

554
00:33:53,281 --> 00:33:54,114
Pardon?

555
00:33:54,115 --> 00:33:55,532
What grade are you?

556
00:33:55,533 --> 00:33:57,952
I'm Grade Five...

557
00:33:59,871 --> 00:34:00,705
I'm Grade One.

558
00:34:01,539 --> 00:34:03,123
I'm a higher grade, and I'm older,

559
00:34:03,124 --> 00:34:06,334
so I hope you'll follow
my instructions carefully.

560
00:34:06,335 --> 00:34:09,087
I ask that you monitor
all the students' social media.

561
00:34:09,088 --> 00:34:10,506
Every single student.

562
00:34:11,174 --> 00:34:12,550
Right now?

563
00:34:16,220 --> 00:34:17,722
By the end of the day.

564
00:34:20,058 --> 00:34:21,642
Grade Five? What's wrong with you?

565
00:34:23,811 --> 00:34:24,812
You haven't served.

566
00:34:26,939 --> 00:34:28,566
Let me know when you're done!

567
00:34:57,178 --> 00:35:00,014
I'm sorry.
I'd like the class for a moment.

568
00:35:07,605 --> 00:35:08,940
Do you recognize these?

569
00:35:09,857 --> 00:35:12,275
They're photos you posted on social media

570
00:35:12,276 --> 00:35:15,238
that were taken illegally and then edited

571
00:35:15,738 --> 00:35:17,323
to mock your teachers.

572
00:35:17,824 --> 00:35:21,577
These prove you spread false information
with malicious intent.

573
00:35:22,078 --> 00:35:25,665
This is a criminal act
that constitutes defamation.

574
00:35:26,415 --> 00:35:28,166
From now on,

575
00:35:28,167 --> 00:35:32,046
the ERPB will crack down
on online violations of teachers' rights.

576
00:35:33,631 --> 00:35:34,631
By the way,

577
00:35:34,632 --> 00:35:37,968
isn't going through our social media
a violation of human rights?

578
00:35:37,969 --> 00:35:40,053
Yeah, this is a human rights violation.

579
00:35:40,054 --> 00:35:43,391
I'm asking whether the ERPB has
that kind of authority.

580
00:35:47,103 --> 00:35:51,607
If you want to know about our authority,
I suggest you visit the ERPB website,

581
00:35:52,108 --> 00:35:55,235
go to "Bureau Introduction,"
and then "Grounds of Establishment."

582
00:35:55,236 --> 00:35:57,237
There, under "Legal Documents,"

583
00:35:57,238 --> 00:36:01,200
you will see the ERPB Establishment Act,
where you can read Article 8.

584
00:36:02,910 --> 00:36:04,077
All right, then.

585
00:36:04,078 --> 00:36:09,332
Those whose names are called,
report to the field!

586
00:36:09,333 --> 00:36:12,794
Stay in formation.

587
00:36:12,795 --> 00:36:15,172
Left flank, march forward!

588
00:36:15,173 --> 00:36:17,299
Left flank!

589
00:36:17,300 --> 00:36:19,384
<i>This is so annoying, seriously!</i>

590
00:36:19,385 --> 00:36:20,678
My legs hurt so damn much.

591
00:36:21,179 --> 00:36:23,305
Hey, who the hell called in the ERPB?

592
00:36:23,306 --> 00:36:24,849
Isn't it obvious?

593
00:36:25,349 --> 00:36:28,144
It's the teachers calling in the ERPB
to back them up.

594
00:36:28,728 --> 00:36:30,396
I don't think so.

595
00:36:32,899 --> 00:36:33,773
What?

596
00:36:33,774 --> 00:36:36,651
Why else would they have come?
There's no reason.

597
00:36:36,652 --> 00:36:39,030
It could be because of Mr. Ko.

598
00:36:40,114 --> 00:36:42,699
Honestly, we all know
he wouldn't do something like that.

599
00:36:42,700 --> 00:36:45,036
And it's not like anyone saw it happen.

600
00:36:49,332 --> 00:36:52,500
Did you guys see it?
Did you see Mr. Ko with Ye-ri?

601
00:36:52,501 --> 00:36:54,337
What are you all talking about?

602
00:36:56,047 --> 00:36:57,173
Is it about me?

603
00:37:00,343 --> 00:37:03,930
We were talking about the ERPB,
wondering when they'd get lost.

604
00:37:05,973 --> 00:37:07,265
It must be hard on you.

605
00:37:07,266 --> 00:37:10,353
They'll be leaving soon enough.
Don't worry about it.

606
00:37:10,853 --> 00:37:11,687
Let's go.

607
00:37:12,772 --> 00:37:14,232
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

608
00:37:21,489 --> 00:37:23,406
HAN YE-RI: GUESS WHO LIVES HERE?

609
00:37:23,407 --> 00:37:25,826
ISN'T THAT YE-RI'S HOMEROOM TEACHER
BACK THERE?

610
00:37:27,370 --> 00:37:30,790
THIS IS SURYEON VILLA NEAR MY PLACE!

611
00:37:46,514 --> 00:37:48,306
MISANG HAGWON

612
00:37:48,307 --> 00:37:49,725
RÉSUMÉ

613
00:37:51,894 --> 00:37:53,770
Are you really thinking of quitting?

614
00:37:53,771 --> 00:37:56,314
There's so much to think about
in a school.

615
00:37:56,315 --> 00:38:00,069
You're dealing with everything
from student support to paperwork.

616
00:38:00,569 --> 00:38:03,155
But in a <i>hagwon,</i>

617
00:38:03,698 --> 00:38:06,449
I feel like you can just focus
on the lessons.

618
00:38:06,450 --> 00:38:08,076
I'm a little surprised.

619
00:38:08,077 --> 00:38:10,328
Our friends made a bet

620
00:38:10,329 --> 00:38:12,747
on which of us would become principal.

621
00:38:12,748 --> 00:38:15,584
You were the clear winner, Seon-yeong.

622
00:38:16,335 --> 00:38:17,878
Yeah, I know.

623
00:38:20,464 --> 00:38:24,552
Well, I thought I'd try enjoying life.

624
00:38:30,558 --> 00:38:34,394
There are many Soyeon Girls' High students
who come to our <i>hagwon.</i>

625
00:38:34,395 --> 00:38:36,522
I did hear about you too.

626
00:38:37,023 --> 00:38:40,775
<i>Hagwons</i> and schools are all the same.
It's not easy here either.

627
00:38:40,776 --> 00:38:43,070
And you've always been tough.

628
00:38:43,571 --> 00:38:45,740
If you really can't take it anymore,
come back.

629
00:38:46,240 --> 00:38:47,616
Let's talk again then.

630
00:38:50,411 --> 00:38:52,079
Okay.

631
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:04,091
Hello.

632
00:39:15,436 --> 00:39:17,187
- Ms. Jung.
- Yes?

633
00:39:17,188 --> 00:39:20,274
I've been solving problems,
but I'm stuck on one.

634
00:39:20,858 --> 00:39:21,776
Let's see.

635
00:39:22,276 --> 00:39:23,693
It's question 18.

636
00:39:23,694 --> 00:39:25,946
I just don't get
why the answer is number three.

637
00:39:26,530 --> 00:39:28,074
Oh, this one?

638
00:39:28,783 --> 00:39:32,787
You need to know the definition
of "combination" to solve this.

639
00:39:33,287 --> 00:39:35,497
Here, 50 choose k equals

640
00:39:35,498 --> 00:39:40,836
50 factorial over k factorial multiplied
by 50 minus k factorial...

641
00:39:45,132 --> 00:39:46,592
So the answer is number three.

642
00:39:48,094 --> 00:39:49,595
This was so confusing.

643
00:39:50,388 --> 00:39:53,181
But you've made it easier to understand.

644
00:39:53,182 --> 00:39:55,350
I should've come to see you earlier.

645
00:39:55,351 --> 00:39:57,311
- Thank you, Ms. Jung.
- Sure.

646
00:39:58,771 --> 00:40:02,316
If I get stuck solving problems again,

647
00:40:02,817 --> 00:40:04,402
could I ask you again?

648
00:40:06,112 --> 00:40:07,029
Yes, of course.

649
00:40:08,239 --> 00:40:09,490
Thank you.

650
00:40:12,952 --> 00:40:13,869
Hello.

651
00:40:20,042 --> 00:40:22,502
So what we learned in the last class is...

652
00:40:22,503 --> 00:40:24,088
Conditional probability.

653
00:40:28,092 --> 00:40:28,926
Yes.

654
00:40:29,468 --> 00:40:33,096
We'll use conditional probability
to solve this problem.

655
00:40:33,097 --> 00:40:37,016
If we choose only natural numbers that are
multiples of two, from one to twelve,

656
00:40:37,017 --> 00:40:38,685
then P(A) would be...

657
00:40:38,686 --> 00:40:40,729
Six over twelve.

658
00:40:43,357 --> 00:40:44,358
Right.

659
00:40:45,025 --> 00:40:47,111
That's right. It's six over twelve.

660
00:40:47,862 --> 00:40:49,612
And P(B) is...

661
00:40:49,613 --> 00:40:51,824
Four over twelve.

662
00:40:52,408 --> 00:40:55,034
The probability of A and B is...

663
00:40:55,035 --> 00:40:56,245
Two over twelve.

664
00:40:56,829 --> 00:40:59,038
Shall we try to solve question two
the same way?

665
00:40:59,039 --> 00:41:00,999
Yes, ma'am.

666
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:02,834
- Who wants to try?
- Kang Min-seo does.

667
00:41:02,835 --> 00:41:04,503
Jin Sang-hui does.

668
00:41:05,713 --> 00:41:06,546
- Min-seo?
- Yes.

669
00:41:06,547 --> 00:41:07,922
- Do you want to try?
- Try it.

670
00:41:07,923 --> 00:41:10,050
Okay. Come up and have a go, Min-seo.

671
00:41:15,097 --> 00:41:16,098
Ms. Jung!

672
00:41:17,183 --> 00:41:19,601
Today's lesson was the best!
I really enjoyed it.

673
00:41:19,602 --> 00:41:21,020
You were epic today.

674
00:41:23,189 --> 00:41:24,106
You're the best!

675
00:41:25,232 --> 00:41:26,192
Ms. Jung.

676
00:41:31,655 --> 00:41:33,573
You must not be so easily swayed.

677
00:41:33,574 --> 00:41:36,702
She's cunning
and may just be gaslighting you.

678
00:41:37,620 --> 00:41:39,246
It'd be best to keep your guard up.

679
00:41:41,665 --> 00:41:42,917
I'm aware of it too.

680
00:41:45,127 --> 00:41:48,172
Whether this is real or just an act,

681
00:41:48,881 --> 00:41:51,258
they're still changing.

682
00:41:53,427 --> 00:41:55,346
I'm so grateful to the ERPB

683
00:41:55,930 --> 00:41:58,015
for even getting us this far.

684
00:41:59,391 --> 00:42:00,518
Thank you.

685
00:42:16,659 --> 00:42:17,576
Ms. Jung.

686
00:42:19,245 --> 00:42:21,579
Ye-ri, what brings you here?

687
00:42:21,580 --> 00:42:23,916
You're probably wondering
why I'm being so nice.

688
00:42:25,125 --> 00:42:29,128
I've wanted to get to know you better
for a while now.

689
00:42:29,129 --> 00:42:31,840
But I felt like
you had the wrong idea about me.

690
00:42:32,424 --> 00:42:34,885
And I didn't know where to start
to clear it up.

691
00:42:35,886 --> 00:42:37,221
So it took me a while.

692
00:42:38,430 --> 00:42:39,348
I'm sorry.

693
00:42:41,308 --> 00:42:42,892
On that note,

694
00:42:42,893 --> 00:42:45,521
how does live streaming sound?

695
00:42:46,730 --> 00:42:47,772
Live streaming?

696
00:42:47,773 --> 00:42:51,401
I want to let people know
that we're on good terms again,

697
00:42:51,402 --> 00:42:55,239
and wouldn't it clear up
some of the misunderstandings about you?

698
00:42:59,618 --> 00:43:01,620
STUDY PLAN

699
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:07,876
YEAR 3, CLASS 4, HAN YE-RI

700
00:43:09,461 --> 00:43:10,545
<i>And in return,</i>

701
00:43:10,546 --> 00:43:14,049
it would be good
if you could speak a bit about the ERPB.

702
00:43:14,842 --> 00:43:15,676
Sorry?

703
00:43:16,260 --> 00:43:18,720
Everyone is having a real hard time
because of it.

704
00:43:18,721 --> 00:43:21,015
They keep asking me for help.

705
00:43:22,349 --> 00:43:25,185
Don't you think they'd love it
if you helped too?

706
00:43:36,822 --> 00:43:37,823
Ms. Jung.

707
00:43:39,617 --> 00:43:42,244
Have you ever cut class before?

708
00:43:43,412 --> 00:43:44,246
Pardon?

709
00:43:44,788 --> 00:43:46,457
Cut class?

710
00:43:55,424 --> 00:43:57,675
My goodness, they're so precious.

711
00:43:57,676 --> 00:43:58,677
Aren't they?

712
00:43:59,261 --> 00:44:01,680
Makes you wonder
where those monstrous kids come from.

713
00:44:03,515 --> 00:44:06,435
What is it that you wanted to say?

714
00:44:07,936 --> 00:44:10,397
How much longer
are you going to put up with this?

715
00:44:11,273 --> 00:44:12,691
Isn't it about time this ended?

716
00:44:18,947 --> 00:44:20,032
ALL THE DOGS FORUM

717
00:44:21,867 --> 00:44:23,242
SCHOOLS THESE DAYS... OMG

718
00:44:23,243 --> 00:44:24,662
Take a look at this.

719
00:44:26,038 --> 00:44:28,082
It's a picture of me that Ye-ri posted.

720
00:44:28,582 --> 00:44:31,250
Time and time again,
I report it, and it gets removed,

721
00:44:31,251 --> 00:44:33,420
but it shows up again somewhere else.

722
00:44:33,921 --> 00:44:37,965
In the end, I'll just get branded
as that kind of person.

723
00:44:37,966 --> 00:44:40,260
I have to live the rest of my life

724
00:44:41,220 --> 00:44:47,017
proving I'm really not that kind of person
and that things weren't as they seemed.

725
00:44:47,518 --> 00:44:50,396
And when I get tired of it,

726
00:44:52,064 --> 00:44:53,232
I'll probably end up

727
00:44:54,149 --> 00:44:55,901
like Mr. Ko.

728
00:45:02,908 --> 00:45:04,993
I'm afraid of the students.

729
00:45:05,911 --> 00:45:09,206
Just seeing Ye-ri's hand on her phone
makes my heart pound.

730
00:45:14,002 --> 00:45:17,548
My fiancée was a teacher.

731
00:45:19,550 --> 00:45:20,968
Two years ago...

732
00:45:24,722 --> 00:45:28,434
she lost her life
at the hands of a student she taught.

733
00:45:31,687 --> 00:45:33,479
<i>We'll start your photo session.</i>

734
00:45:33,480 --> 00:45:35,691
Okay. Bride, you're looking great.

735
00:45:36,191 --> 00:45:37,358
Okay.

736
00:45:37,359 --> 00:45:39,861
Groom, you should look at the bride too.

737
00:45:39,862 --> 00:45:41,821
- Right.
- That's great.

738
00:45:41,822 --> 00:45:43,866
Groom, hold your arm higher.

739
00:46:54,686 --> 00:46:55,604
Ga-yun.

740
00:46:59,316 --> 00:47:00,859
Ga-yun, I'm here.

741
00:47:32,641 --> 00:47:34,351
Thank you for waiting for me.

742
00:48:10,762 --> 00:48:13,973
So I truly understand
the fear you're feeling

743
00:48:13,974 --> 00:48:17,519
after what happened to Mr. Ko.

744
00:48:19,313 --> 00:48:21,440
But that's why I am asking this of you.

745
00:48:21,940 --> 00:48:23,901
It's not for your sake.

746
00:48:25,569 --> 00:48:28,739
It's for the sake of the kids you teach.

747
00:48:36,705 --> 00:48:37,915
Ms. Jung.

748
00:48:38,457 --> 00:48:40,500
Why do you think we came here?

749
00:48:42,836 --> 00:48:43,837
Of course,

750
00:48:44,379 --> 00:48:46,839
because of Mr. Ko...

751
00:48:46,840 --> 00:48:48,842
No, we are here because of you.

752
00:48:53,472 --> 00:48:57,309
The kids requested that we save you.

753
00:48:59,019 --> 00:49:00,437
Year 3, class 4.

754
00:49:01,521 --> 00:49:04,232
They're students in your homeroom class.

755
00:49:05,901 --> 00:49:07,860
REPORTS RELATED TO SOYEON GIRLS' HIGH

756
00:49:07,861 --> 00:49:13,115
<i>Hello. I am Park Su-jin,
a student at Soyeon Girls' High School.</i>

757
00:49:13,116 --> 00:49:14,575
<i>When I saw strange rumors</i>

758
00:49:14,576 --> 00:49:18,537
<i>and slanderous posts spreading
about our homeroom teacher,</i>

759
00:49:18,538 --> 00:49:22,458
<i>I was so upset and angry
that I decided to write this letter.</i>

760
00:49:22,459 --> 00:49:26,337
<i>After a post was shared
claiming Ms. Jung wasn't teaching,</i>

761
00:49:26,338 --> 00:49:28,756
<i>the whole school fell into chaos.</i>

762
00:49:28,757 --> 00:49:30,758
<i>But the claim just isn't true.</i>

763
00:49:30,759 --> 00:49:35,012
<i>We want to see her teach
with full passion again, like before.</i>

764
00:49:35,013 --> 00:49:38,266
<i>Please protect
Ms. Jung's honor and rights.</i>

765
00:49:38,767 --> 00:49:43,437
<i>Please take this situation seriously
and protect teachers like Ms. Jung,</i>

766
00:49:43,438 --> 00:49:46,483
<i>who quietly devote themselves
to supporting their students</i>

767
00:49:47,192 --> 00:49:49,736
<i>and ensuring they are no longer harmed.</i>

768
00:49:50,237 --> 00:49:52,364
<i>I ask you with utmost sincerity.</i>

769
00:49:58,620 --> 00:50:00,038
Stop it.

770
00:50:02,624 --> 00:50:05,877
I WISH I COULD LISTEN TO HER CLASS

771
00:50:11,049 --> 00:50:15,762
<i>I don't think playing the same game
meant they felt the same way.</i>

772
00:50:16,263 --> 00:50:17,263
I FEEL BAD FOR OUR TEACHER

773
00:50:17,264 --> 00:50:20,809
<i>There are some kids
who are as afraid of Ye-ri as you are.</i>

774
00:50:21,309 --> 00:50:23,687
